Ο QUEEN of Paphos, leave thy home In Cyprus' flowery isle,

And come to Glycera's shrine at Rome, To grace it with thy smile.

And with thee bring thy roguish boy, But not without his darts,

And in thy train the Graces coy, And all thy loving hearts.

Tmo.

If thou wilt only kiss her, ah !
